While loop

Whenever we want execute block of code again and again it is called as loop.
The code of block will execute repeatedly until the given condition is true.

1. While
2. Condition
3. Colon
4. Starting on next line

syntax : 

While condition:
   block of code

It looks similar to the if statement but there is difference of how they behave.
In if statement at the end of block execution will continue after block of code while in while loop
The execution will jump back to the starting line of while statement.


Example

value = 0
while value < 5 :
   print("hello")
print( "this is not part of while loop" )

